<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <!-- Get bootstrap library for styling -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/bootstrap.min.css" />
    <title>The Average Olympian</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container p-3">
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
            <ol class="breadcrumb">
                <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/sports">All Sports</a></li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">The Average olympian</li>
            </ol>
        </nav>
        <h1>Average Olympian in <%=data.name%></h1>
        The table below shows the statistics of the average athlete in <%=data.name%>. This
        statistics elucidate what a typical athlete in this sport would look like.
        <table class = "table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Name of Sport</th>
                    <th>Height (cm)</th>
                    <th>Weight (kg)</th>
                    <th>Age</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tr>
                <td><%=data.name%></td>
                <!-- Reference: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58269113/how-to-round-the-numerical-output-value-in-ejs -->
                <% for (var i = 1; i < Object.keys(data).length; i++) {
                    var key = Object.keys(data)[i]; %>
                                    <td><%= parseFloat(data[key]).toFixed(1)%> </td>
                <% }; %>
        </tr>
        </table>
    </div>
</body>
</html>